rgence of a state sponsored disability advocacy organization and the lives of chinese men who have trouble walking in recent years kohrman has been conducting research projects aimed at analyzing and intervening in the biopolitics of cigarette smoking and production these projects expand upon analytical themes of kohrman's disability research and engage in novel ways techniques of public health other affiliations department of anthropology events & presentations cigarette citadels remapping theory and policy cigarette factories in and outside of china january 30 2012 shorenstein aparc seminar series matthew kohrman research programs & projects a sense of crisis as china confronts ailments of affluence project global tobacco prevention research initiative project new steps for tobacco control in and outside of china project search ahpp recent commentary exploring china's formidable cigarette industry february 17 2012 shorenstein aparc ahpp scp news kohrman to speak about cigarette factory mapping and policy january 18 2012 shorenstein aparc scp announcement kohrman's ground breaking study of cigarette warning labels shorenstein aparc ahpp scp in the news stanford cancer center news on june 7 2011 give new smoking ban time suggests china tobacco health expert matthew kohrman may 11 2011 shorenstein aparc ahpp scp in the news npr and al jazeera english tobacco control efforts in china and beyond recent work of ahpp faculty affiliate matthew kohrman may 6 2011 shorenstein aparc in the news more commentary about matthew kohrman news around the web china dependent on tobacco in more ways than one the industry in china is run by the tobacco monopoly administration a central government administrative body created in the 1980s also known as china tobacco corp says stanford university's matthew kohrman who has researched smoking in china for february 18 2011 in npr stanford researcher's online map pinpoints cigarette factories around the world stanford anthropologist matthew 